                <h1>How to Easily Apply Peel and Stick Wallpaper</h1>
                <p>Applying peel and stick wallpaper is simple and effective. Start with a clean, smooth wall surface, and gather essential tools: a squeegee and a utility knife. Measure and cut the wallpaper roll, then peel a few inches of the backing. Align it with your wall, press firmly, and smoothly squeegee from the center out to eliminate bubbles. Trim excess edges for a clean finish.</p>
